Leaders have called on the team appointed to spearhead unity in the country to boldly address all issues causing disunity and political suspicion. The leaders, who included Governor James Ongwae and Senator Sam Ongeri, advised the 14-member team not to shy away from advising President Uhuru Kenyatta and Opposition leader Raila Odinga on how to heal the nation. ALSO READ:

Raila calls off economic boycott They said the newly found unity between Kenyatta and Raila gave the country the best opportunity to address challenges that have caused bloodshed and hatred among Kenyans since independence. Speaking during the Annual General Meeting of the Abagusii Cultural Development Council in Kisii town yesterday, the leaders pledged to support the unity team. Other leaders from the region who supported the Raila-Uhuru peace pact included Deputy Governor Joash Maangi, Kitutu Chache South MP Richard Onyonka and Nyaribari Masaba MP Ezekiel Machogu. The leaders said Kenyans were banking their hopes on the team for a united country. Avoid fake news! Subscribe to the Standard SMS service and receive factual, verified breaking news as it happens. Text the word 'NEWS' to 22840 “We would like to appreciate the decision by the two leaders to appoint the chairman of the Gusii council of elders James Matundura and academician Florence Omosa to be part of this great team,” said Governor Ongwae. Ongwae said the newfound unity had helped cool down political temperatures in the country.